00:42:45.960 --> 00:42:49.310
How do you present this info to
the people who you're auditing for

00:42:53.930 --> 00:42:54.850
if you do at all?

00:43:01.640 --> 00:43:04.500
>> LAZAR: I'll tell you
honestly, my idea is

00:43:04.500 --> 00:43:10.610
to become an accessibility tester and
to start a career as a consultant.

00:43:10.610 --> 00:43:11.610
Why not?

00:43:12.100 --> 00:43:14.880
I do provide those services.

00:43:14.880 --> 00:43:18.540
So far, I did it via Zoom
calls and then video.

00:43:19.640 --> 00:43:23.300
I most likely share the
screen and tell what's wrong

00:43:23.300 --> 00:43:24.460
and what should be fixed.

00:43:25.930 --> 00:43:30.950
This was the way I used to do
it, but if some people

00:43:30.950 --> 00:43:35.870
or clients have some different--
how to say, wishes, desires,

00:43:35.870 --> 00:43:39.910
so maybe they want to have
all documented or screen

00:43:39.910 --> 00:43:46.090
and audio recorded, I'll be more
than happy to provide this as well.

00:43:49.610 --> 00:43:51.820
>> ANDRIJA: I can only add to that.

00:43:53.170 --> 00:43:57.540
I'm obviously not providing
that service as a service.

00:43:57.540 --> 00:44:03.940
However,
if I need to help a developer

00:44:03.941 --> 00:44:06.240
make something more accessible,

00:44:06.240 --> 00:44:13.190
I will give him a basic set of
tools, and I will inspect the code,

00:44:13.190 --> 00:44:15.140
which is present on the website.

00:44:16.930 --> 00:44:21.840
Then I will create the list of
all the issues with the structure

00:44:21.840 --> 00:44:24.150
of the web website.

00:44:24.150 --> 00:44:30.140
Of course, this is just the
list of structural issues.

00:44:30.140 --> 00:44:35.150
This is not the actual
accessibility test of the website.

00:44:35.150 --> 00:44:39.830
I'm giving them indication, 'Hey,
guys, you are using wrong governments

00:44:39.830 --> 00:44:40.820
for this.

00:44:40.820 --> 00:44:43.280
You're basically
asking for trouble.

00:44:43.280 --> 00:44:44.960
Please use these elements instead."

00:44:44.960 --> 00:44:49.100
Or, "Please try this
solution or that source."

00:44:49.100 --> 00:44:50.354
That's my answer to that.

00:44:52.800 --> 00:44:58.580
>> DANIELLE: I think to leave
us with one final thought.

00:44:58.580 --> 00:45:01.810
You guys both had really
awesome takeaways,

00:45:01.810 --> 00:45:08.180
and there were so many things,
messages for developers and people

00:45:08.180 --> 00:45:10.170
who have their websites.

00:45:10.170 --> 00:45:12.620
If you had one thing
to say to somebody,

00:45:13.790 --> 00:45:18.700
if they didn't take away anything
at all, give them one thing

00:45:18.700 --> 00:45:22.170
from each of you,
what would that be?

00:45:31.929 --> 00:45:33.080
>> LAZAR: Andrija, maybe you can--

00:45:37.635 --> 00:45:43.070
>> ANDRIJA: If there was one thing
that I would say is basically,

00:45:43.070 --> 00:45:44.270
don't be afraid.

00:45:44.270 --> 00:45:50.380
Just learn, dive into the
topic, and realize

00:45:50.380 --> 00:45:53.440
that we have a great
responsibility in our hands.

00:45:54.840 --> 00:46:02.980
It is our mission to make sure
that online presence is accessible

00:46:02.980 --> 00:46:03.560
to anyone.

00:46:05.363 --> 00:46:07.910
>> LAZAR: I would say start small.

00:46:09.540 --> 00:46:12.560
Small steps are crucial here.

00:46:12.560 --> 00:46:17.490
You don't have to make the entire
website accessible at once,

00:46:17.490 --> 00:46:19.040
just tiny steps.

00:46:20.810 --> 00:46:24.200
Do whatever you can
little by little.

00:46:24.200 --> 00:46:27.590
Follow the latest trends,
dedicate yourself.

00:46:27.590 --> 00:46:29.240
It's not rocket science.

00:46:29.240 --> 00:46:30.240
It's not hard.

00:46:30.240 --> 00:46:31.822
[chuckles]

00:46:31.822 --> 00:46:37.070
Everything will be accessible
shortly, but please just start.

00:46:37.070 --> 00:46:39.420
That would be one word so start.

00:46:39.420 --> 00:46:40.340
>> DANIELLE: I love that.

00:46:40.340 --> 00:46:41.300
I love both of those.

00:46:41.300 --> 00:46:43.140
Those are so important.

00:46:43.140 --> 00:46:45.920
It looks like we have
a question submission.

00:46:47.280 --> 00:46:50.930
What is important to you when
doing an accessibility test?

00:46:50.930 --> 00:46:55.100
What should the people inquiring
for the test think about?

00:46:55.100 --> 00:46:57.400
I think you covered
this a little bit.

00:46:57.400 --> 00:47:00.320
When somebody's going into a test,
what should they be keeping in mind?

00:47:07.925 --> 00:47:11.670
>> LAZAR: I'm talking from a
screen reader user perspective.

00:47:11.670 --> 00:47:13.560
Headings are very important.

00:47:14.700 --> 00:47:18.940
All added fields should be labeled.

00:47:18.940 --> 00:47:25.119
Combo boxes,
checkboxes that all pictures,

00:47:25.120 --> 00:47:29.430
graphics all text is included

00:47:29.430 --> 00:47:31.170
to all pictures and images.

00:47:33.040 --> 00:47:34.400
Buttons.

00:47:34.400 --> 00:47:35.120
That's important.

00:47:35.120 --> 00:47:38.860
It depends on what the
site is presenting.

00:47:41.750 --> 00:47:47.160
Andrija sometimes said like, "Try to
imagine that your website is a book.

00:47:47.160 --> 00:47:49.350
It's like chapters.

00:47:49.350 --> 00:47:54.740
Do your best to make it readily
early available to all people

00:47:54.740 --> 00:47:56.930
so people can read it easily."

00:47:59.110 --> 00:48:03.816
>> ANDRIJA: I would just like
to add that the information

00:48:03.840 --> 00:48:06.650
that is presented to
a screen reader user

00:48:07.940 --> 00:48:13.380
if accessibility is not done right,
can very often be overwhelming.

00:48:15.450 --> 00:48:20.070
If a website is showing
an access of information

00:48:20.070 --> 00:48:23.490
to the screen reader
user, then the interaction

00:48:23.490 --> 00:48:24.960
with the website will be slow.

00:48:27.703 --> 00:48:32.792
By that, they will know
I had to spend more time

00:48:32.793 --> 00:48:34.710
to purchase this product.

00:48:34.710 --> 00:48:36.110
I could go to that store.

00:48:37.480 --> 00:48:40.970
The process would take five
minutes, 10 minutes.

00:48:42.630 --> 00:48:43.800
Time is of the essence.

00:48:45.360 --> 00:48:49.270
Try to focus on what's important.

00:48:49.270 --> 00:48:55.170
Whatever can be distracting should
not be read by a screen reader.

00:48:56.430 --> 00:49:02.130
You need to think about how
you will design a website.

00:49:03.690 --> 00:49:05.730
You need to focus on the basics.

00:49:05.730 --> 00:49:10.450
If website is able to
serve its basic function.

00:49:10.450 --> 00:49:15.320
If you can make a
purchase of the website,

00:49:16.380 --> 00:49:21.470
then the website serves
its basic purpose.

00:49:21.470 --> 00:49:26.010
Then you can focus on other things.

00:49:26.010 --> 00:49:30.230
If you cannot make a purpose, if
there is an issue that prevents it,

00:49:31.720 --> 00:49:36.660
you could have spent
months testing a website,

00:49:36.660 --> 00:49:40.640
making sure it is accessible,
but if it has that critical favor

00:49:40.640 --> 00:49:43.116
that screen reader user
cannot purchase it,

00:49:43.117 --> 00:49:45.310
basically,
all that testing is in way.

